  "plainText": "Don't Starve\nTogether\nLiving Log\nFood Info\n0\n0\n0\nWood\n(non-survivor food)\nObject Info\n45 sec.\nCan be Burned\n20\nSource\nDropped by\nCrafting\nWormwoodWandering Trader\nDescription\nPut yourself into your work.\n×20 ( only)\nFilters\nTier\nAlways available\nDescription\nLife wood be a scream...\nx3\nFilters\nTier\nMiscellaneous\n\"livinglog\"\n“It looks worried.”\n–Wilson\n“It looks upset.”\n–Willow\n“Creepy face log!”\n–Wolfgang\n“It is forever screaming silently.”\n–Wendy\n“EVEN WORSE THAN A NORMAL LOG”\n–WX-78\n“This log is special.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“I want to keep you, and call you \"Frank\".”\n–Woodie\n“I like the noise they make when you burn them.”\n–Maxwell\n“Burning such magic wöuld seem a waste.”\n–Wigfrid\n“This log has a face.”\n–Webber\n“Magic building blocks!”\n–Warly\n“Friend. Nice friend”\n–Wormwood\n“Stop looking at me like that.”\n–Winona\n“Don't look at me with those sad eyes!”\n–Wortox\n“Feel kinda bad, florp...”\n–Wurt\n“Yep, this log's definitely haunted.”\n–Walter\n“This log is a lot livelier than it should be.”\n–Wanda\nLiving Logs are Items dropped by Treeguards, Poison Birchnut Trees and Mush Gnomes. They can also be obtained by chopping down Totally Normal Trees, the stump of Totally Normal Tree can be dug for another Living Log. Wormwood can always \"craft\" Living Logs at the cost of 20 Health.\nThey are used to craft several magic items, including a Shadow Manipulator, and can also be used as fuel for a Fire. Living Logs will scream when burned on a fire or when eaten by a Cookie Cutter.\nA Living Log may be used to repair a Wood Wall. This works in a similar fashion to using a standard log, except that the Living Log repairs three times the wall health of a standard log.\nUsage[edit | edit source]\n×2\n×4\n×68\n×3\n×7\n×5\n×2\n×4\n×2\n×4\n×4\n×8\n×2\n×4\n×2\n×2\n×4\n×2\n×3\n×4\n×4\n×2\n×4\n×3\n×2\n×2\n×4\n×2\n×4\n×2\n×3\n×5\n×20\nOnly during the Event: Hallowed Nights\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nThe Living Log's scream was added in the The End of the Beginning update.\nResourcesCraftable Items\nView or edit this template\nResources\nAttention: The following categories are only for the players look up the page based on their first impression, they have nothing to do with the actual categories/behavior/function/tags of these items\nPlants\nNatural non-living materials\nMobs Parts\nSkins\nFeathers\nBones and horns\nGems\nShadow Resources\nLunar Resources\nCraftable Resources\nNon-natural materials\nTrinkets\nLost Relics\nTransmission Items\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Together Craftable Items\nRegular Filters\nSurvivor Items\nWilson\nWillow\nWolfgang\nWendy\nWX-78\nWickerbottom\nWoodie\nWes\nMaxwell\nWigfrid\nWebber\nWarly\nWortox\nWormwood\nWinona\nWurt\nWalter\nWanda\nTools\nLight Sources\nPrototypers & Stations\nRefined Materials\nWeapons\nArmor\nClothing\nHealing\nMagic\nDecorations\nStructures\nStorage Solutions\nCooking\nFood & Gardening\nFishing\nSeafaring\nBeefalo Riding\nWinter Items\nSummer Items\nRain Gear\nCrafting Station Filters\nSpecial Event\nAncient Pseudoscience\nCarpentry\nCartography\nCritters\nCelestial\nBrightsmithy\nShadowcraft\nFabrication\nBottle Exchange\nCombrining Filter\nTea Brewing Filter\nSculptures\nSeasonings\nTrading\nTrading Hutch\nOfferings\nCawnival Creation\nTrinket Trove\nMad Science\nWinter's Feast Cooking\nSanctum Smithy Filter\nCustom Course Shack Filter",
